post_text:
Parents of Online Learners,

Within the next few weeks you will begin receiving weekly email updates from Edgenuity on your child’s progress in each of their courses.

In addition to the progress emails, we suggest that you check your child’s dashboard regularly. Through the dashboard you have access to their progress and grade for each course. For a more detailed breakdown of what your student completes in a day, you can access this information by clicking “student profile” and then “attendance report.” The attendance report will list the amount of time spent on each course as well as the number of assignments submitted. Idle time is the time spent logged in, but not active. If you have questions pertaining to any of this information, please contact one of their instructors.

tiffany.wadsworth@imagineprep.com
jordan.madura@imagineprep.com
david.williams@imagineprep.com
sarah.madison@imagineprep.com

Thank you for partnering with us to support your child’s online learning experience.

Imagine Prep Families,

At this time we are planning bus routes for when we return in-person. We want to make sure that all in-person families needing transportation are getting bus stop information. As a reminder, if you are a hybrid student or completing your classes through Edgenuity you do not need to respond to this email.

If you do need transportation, please email Ms. Desiree at desiree.boisvert@imagineprep.com with the address that student/s will be picked up and dropped off at. Please respond by August 19, 2020 to ensure a spot on a bus.

The walk zone is South of Apache Trail, West of Idaho, North of US 60 and East of Meridian. If you live in the walk zone, bus service is NOT provided for am or pm routes.

Please be aware that these routes will be for Semester 1.

Based on in-person enrollment requests for Semester 2, bus routes may need to be adjusted.

post_text:
Please give a warm welcome to another new member of the Imagine Prep family! #pantherpride

Hello, my name is Ms. Brittany Foster and I am honored to a part of the Imagine Prep Superstition family.

This will be my 8th year teaching at the secondary level. I earned my Masters of Science in Curriculum and Instruction from Western Governors University, and my Bachelor of Arts in English (emphasis in both Literature & Writing) from the University of Arkansas at Little Rock. I am also a licensed English 7-12 English teacher in Arkansas, and currently working on obtaining my Arizona certification.

My favorite thing about teaching is helping students realize their invaluable worth and how important each of their voices are.

When I am not in the classroom, I enjoy volunteering, attending comic-cons, exploring museums, and of course reading and writing.

I am excited and looking forward to supporting the success of all students at IPS. Go Panthers!

post_text:
Imagine Prep is super excited to welcome a new member to the “Panther Family”! Mr. Kyle Schutrum. You may remember Mr. Schutrum as one of our substitute teachers from last year, but this year he his joining the high school math team! Welcome Mr. Schutrum!

My name is Kyle Schutrum. I have a bachelor’s degree in Bioengineering from Syracuse University. This will be my first year teaching, but I have one year of prior substitute teaching experience. I moved to the valley from Buffalo, NY in 2015. In the past I worked at a small actuarial firm and gave food tours of Phoenix and Scottsdale in my spare time. I love hiking and running! I just ran my first marathon last year in Mesa.

post_text:
As a result of Governor Ducey’s Executive Order on Monday, Imagine Schools is revising our plans to reopen our schools. We understand you may have questions and concerns. post_text:
Dear Panthers,

The IPS Key Club would like to send out a positive message to help everyone get through this difficult time.

We know that switching to virtual learning is very hard for all of the students and staff. As a club focused on service, we feel the need to let you all know that we will get through this and we will be made better because of it. To the students, keep in mind that even though we are not sitting in classrooms, everything still counts towards your grade. This is especially important for the seniors, in order to graduate. Seniors, we understand how hard this may be on you all. It is important to keep your spirits up and persevere through the changes to the end of the year.

We also want to show our support to the teachers and admin through all of this. You are all working very hard to continue to set us up for success, even with everything else going on. We send all of our gratitude.

As some departing words, we want to leave you with a quote: “Tough situations build strong people”. #pantherpride

Sincerely,
IPS Key Club

To the students, keep in mind that even though we are not sitting in classrooms, everything still counts towards your grade. This is especially important for the seniors, in order to graduate. Seniors, we understand how hard this may be on you all. It is important to keep your spirits up and persevere through the changes to the end of the year.

We also want to show our support to the teachers and admin through all of this. You are all working very hard to continue to set us up for success, even with everything else going on. We send all of our gratitude.

As some departing words, we want to leave you with a quote: “Tough situations build strong people”. #pantherpride

Sincerely,
IPS Key Club

post_text: Imagine Prep Superstition's head wrestling coach was named the 2019-2020 CAA wrestling coach of the year for the second year in a row. The CAA wanted to recognize this momentous achievement as well as his inspirational work as a coach. Kevin Glascock has been coaching wrestling for 11 years, 3 years as the head coach for Imagine Prep Superstition. This year the team became back-to-back state champions. Along with a rigorous action plan for developing these young athletes to become championship caliber wrestlers, Glascock also instill strong values in his team. Honesty, integrity, focus and work ethic are among the values that he expects from the team in all facets of their life. Because of this, not only were they state champions, but they also have an average team GPA of 3.5. Coach Glascock is "honored to receive this award because it serves as a testament to my team that I am here for them and I do my absolute best to push them to reach their maximum potential." Congratulations Coach Glascock! We are lucky to have you as part of the Imagine Family!!

Our STEM classes are raising money for some of our new & upcoming courses that will be offered next year. We will be selling Little Caesar items such as pizza kits, crazy bread, & desserts. Payments must be made at the time the order is placed. To place an order online, please visit
PizzaKit.com and enter our Fundraiser ID # 381996. All orders are due by March 6th. The top 10 sellers will receive awards and prizes. 1st, 2nd, & 3rd place winners will receive additional prizes. Orders will be delivered the week of March 23rd in the STEM Lab. The fundraising participants will be responsible for delivering all order items. If you are interested in placing and picking up your order please contact: sarah.madison@imagineprep.com. Thank you in advance for your support of our STEM program!
